Oh!
We've got another one.

01:31.258 --> 01:33.358
Cool. Let me dig it up.
Oh, there's a good lad.

01:33.360 --> 01:35.994
BUFORD: Wait.
It's not a nail,
it's a coin!

01:35.996 --> 01:37.930
Well, let's have
a look then, huh?

01:37.932 --> 01:39.698
Oh, yes,
I've seen this before.

01:39.700 --> 01:40.933
It's a commemorative coin

01:40.935 --> 01:43.836
from the 1903
Danville World's Fair.

01:43.838 --> 01:47.272
Many steam-driven
devices were introduced
to the world back then.

01:47.274 --> 01:49.007
It must've been
quite an event!

01:49.342 --> 01:50.742
